      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Stop immediately: Switching from sertraline to St. John's wort is extremely dangerous because the two drugs can interact severely to lower the effectiveness of birth control, antidepressants you might start later, and your metabolism of vital hormones. Additionally, St. John's wort is not intended for severe anxiety and carries a high risk of causing a serotonin syndrome or withdrawal symptoms if you discontinue sertraline abruptly. You should not make any medication changes immediately instead contacting your prescribing doctor to manage your nausea before making any new switches.",
